Interface IDoubleDataSet<WINDOW extends ILabeledDataWindow<double[]>>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IDereferencer<String,WINDOW>, IItemReferenceIterable<WINDOW>, ILabeledDataSet<double[],WINDOW>, IShuffleIterable<WINDOW>, ISizedIterable<WINDOW>, Iterable<WINDOW>

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ComposedSoundDataSet, ComposedStoredSoundDataSet

    public interface IDoubleDataSet<WINDOW extends ILabeledDataWindow<double[]>>
extends ILabeledDataSet<double[],WINDOW>
    Holds a set of double data window references with associated labeling and tagging. Allows both shuffleable iteration and direct access to the contained references via IDereferencer.loadReference(Object). The data set may be examined in total to get the full set of contained label names and label values for any of the contained label names.
